In England, in the seven days to 09 March, there were 33,033 new confirmed cases (58.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 March, there were 39,430 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (6,397 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 March is 3,727,585 (6,622.5 cases per 100,000 population).
